# Supabase Guidance

Read these before changing Supabase access:

- `docs/DATABASE.md` for current tables, RPCs, realtime subscriptions, tenant gaps, and schema conventions.
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for the read/write service split and data flow.
- `docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md` for error handling and Server Action rules.

Keep this rule short. Do not copy database details here.

## Non-Negotiables

- Server code (services, mutations, Server Components) uses `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server`; Client Components use `@/lib/supabase/client`. No shared singleton.
- Resolve the tenant via `getCurrentHotelId()` from `@/lib/tenant`; never hardcode a hotel id. Every read/write filters by `hotel_id`.
- Reads stay in `*.service.ts`; writes stay in `*.mutations.ts`.
- Mutation files start with `"use server"` and call `revalidatePath`.
- Business rules stay in service/mutation helpers, not UI components.
- RLS is the second line of defense (see `supabase/migrations/`); keep app-layer scoping too.
